==Awards== Four of the Telarc P. D. Q. Bach recordings received Grammy awards in the Best Comedy Recording category. These were the four albums released from 1989 until 1992.<ref>[http://www.presser.com/composers/info.cfm?Name=PETERSCHICKELE Biography page] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060723152819/http://www.presser.com/Composers/info.cfm?Name=PETERSCHICKELE |date=2006-07-23 }} for [[Peter Schickele]] on Theodore Press Company's website</ref> Schickele also received a Grammy nomination in the Best Comedy Album category in 1996 for his abridged audiobook edition of ''The Definitive Biography of P. D. Q. Bach''.<ref>[http://theenvelope.latimes.com/extras/lostmind/year/1996/1996grammy.htm Past Winners Database] page for the 1996 Grammy award nominees and winners on the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' website</ref>
